    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT, CONNECTING
        RODS AND PISTONS - Crankshaft and Main Bearings - Cleaning
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Cleaning</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the crankshaft with a suitable solvent. Dry the crankshaft with filtered compressed
                air.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a stiff nylon brush to clean all of the internal oil passages of the crankshaft. Loosen
                all dirt, sludge, and other deposits that may have accumulated. Flush the oil passages with a suitable
                non-caustic solvent. Dry the oil passages with filtered compressed air.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the bearing caps and inserts thoroughly in solvent. Dry with filtered compressed
                air.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
